636
00:26:56,040 --> 00:26:58,040
of motion, or it can be oriented opposite

637
00:26:58,040 --> 00:27:00,040
to the direction of motion.

638
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:02,040
In quantum mechanics, of course,

639
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:04,040
if the spin is oriented in some other direction,

640
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:06,040
you can build it up out of superpositions

641
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:08,040
of the two states along the direction of motion

642
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:10,040
and opposite.

643
00:27:10,040 --> 00:27:12,040
So an electron moving along with a high momentum,

644
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:14,040
for example, can either have its spin

645
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,040
along the direction of motion,

646
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:20,040
that means it's rotating with a right hand screw thread.

647
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:25,040
It's rotating or spinning with a right hand screw thread,

648
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:28,040
that's called a right-handed electron.

649
00:27:28,040 --> 00:27:31,040
And an electron can also be a left-handed electron.

